str:Codelist.com:Name: Frequency
str:Codelist.com:Description: This code list provides a set of values indicating the "frequency" of the data (e.g. weekly, monthly, quarterly). The concept â??frequencyâ?? may refer to various stages in the production process, e.g. data collection or data dissemination. For example, a time series could be disseminated at annual frequency but the underlying data are compiled monthly. The code list is applicable for all different uses of "frequency". This code list was formally adopted on 4 December 2013. More information about and supporting material for this code list and SDMX code lists in general (e.g. list of generic codes for expressing general concepts like "Total", "Unknown", etc.; syntaxes for the creation of further codes; general guidelines for the creation of SDMX code lists) can be found at this address: http://sdmx.org/?page_id=1513.

str:Codelist.com:Name: Observation Status
str:Codelist.com:Description: This code list provides coded information on 1) the quality of a value or 2) unusual or missing values. It was formally adopted on 15 September 2016. More information about this code list and SDMX code lists in general (e.g. list of generic codes for expressing general concepts like "Total", "Unknown", etc.; syntaxes for the creation of further codes; general guidelines for the creation of SDMX code lists) can be found at this address: https://sdmx.org/?page_id=4345.

str:Concept.com:Name: Source details
str:Concept.com:Description: Information on the name and specific details of each observation's data source. Both the sources for the numerator and denominator could be specified here.

str:Concept.com:Name: Reporting type
str:Concept.com:Description: Represents whether the official SDG series is reported by a national, regional, or international agency.

str:Concept.com:Name: Lower bound value
str:Concept.com:Description: Lower bound value for the indicator or series.

str:Concept.com:Name: Upper bound value
str:Concept.com:Description: Upper bound value for the indicator or series.

str:Concept.com:Name: Time period or range (ISO8601)
str:Concept.com:Description: ISO8601 representation of the actual time interval to which the observation refers

str:Concept.com:Name: Observation-level footnotes
str:Concept.com:Description: Additional information on specific aspects of each observation, such as how the observation was computed/estimated or details that could affect the comparability of this data point with others in a time series.

str:Concept.com:Name: Time period details
str:Concept.com:Description: When TIME_PERIOD refers to a date range, this attribute is used to provide metadata on the actual range the observation refers to (e.g. for period '2001-2003' TIME_PERIOD would be 2002 but the actual dates --2001-2003-- would be expressed here).

str:Concept.com:Name: Nature of data points
str:Concept.com:Description: Information on the production and dissemination of the data (e.g.: if the figure has been produced by the country, estimated by an international agency, etc.)

str:Concept.com:Name: Disability status
str:Concept.com:Description: Represents a person's disability status.

str:Concept.com:Name: Composite breakdown
str:Concept.com:Description: Represents an amalgamation of infrequently used breakdowns.

str:Concept.com:Name: Custom Breakdown
str:Concept.com:Description: Used to represent user-defined breakdowns.

str:Concept.com:Name: Income or wealth quantile
str:Concept.com:Description: Income or wealth quantile

str:Concept.com:Name: Degree of urbanisation
str:Concept.com:Description: Refers to Total, Urban, or Rural location.

str:Concept.com:Name: SDG Series
str:Concept.com:Description: SDG Indicator or Series. Uses the CETS convention for encoding.

str:Concept.com:Name: Base period
str:Concept.com:Description: Period of time used as the base of an index number, or to which a constant series refers.

str:Concept.com:Name: Unit of measure
str:Concept.com:Description: Unit in which the data values are expressed.

str:Concept.com:Name: Unit multiplier
str:Concept.com:Description: Exponent in base 10 specified so that multiplying the observation numeric values by 10^UNIT_MULT gives a value expressed in the unit of measure.

str:Concept.com:Name: Observation value
str:Concept.com:Description: Value of a particular variable.

str:Concept.com:Name: Observation status
str:Concept.com:Description: Information on the quality of a value or an unusual or missing value.

str:Concept.com:Name: Time period
str:Concept.com:Description: Timespan or point in time to which the observation actually refers.

str:Concept.com:Name: Occupation
str:Concept.com:Description: Job or position held by an individual who performs a set of tasks and duties.

str:Concept.com:Name: Education level
str:Concept.com:Description: Highest level of an educational programme the person has successfully completed.

str:Concept.com:Name: Age
str:Concept.com:Description: Length of time that an entity has lived or existed.

str:Concept.com:Name: Sex
str:Concept.com:Description: State of being male or female.

str:Concept.com:Name: Reference area
str:Concept.com:Description: Country or geographic area to which the measured statistical phenomenon relates.

str:Concept.com:Name: Frequency of observation
str:Concept.com:Description: Time interval at which observations occur over a given time period.
